Responsabilidades:
            •	To familiarize and manage course resources;
To follow lesson plans for students and preparing for the deliverance of the lessons; 
•	To deliver lessons on time, format and according to schedule;
•	To ensure the safe custody and optimum use of resources and equipment, provided by the Centre, used during lessons;
•	To ensure that the classroom stays orderly and students stay motivated;
•	To assign work, correcting and marking work carried out by students;
•	To write progress reports for students and grade student homework and tests; 
•	To identify, address and report on students’ needs and difficulties;
•	To identify and report on own’s needs to the line supervisor and actively participate in addressing and meeting those needs to ensure personal and professional wellbeing;
•	To assist in the creation and production of tests and resources for students;
•	To record students’ assistance and participation in class.

Funciones:
            •	To teach and educate students according to guidelines provided;
•	To teach and educate students according to the educational needs, abilities and attainment potential of individual students;
•	To help students improve their listening, speaking, reading and writing skills;
•	To communicate, consult and co-operate with other members of the staff, in order to ensure the best interest of students; 
•	With critical thinking to review and evaluate one’s own teaching, learning and personal development; 
•	To actively engage with ongoing training and to participate in performance reviews;
•	To advise and co-operate with the Head of Centre, Heads of Department, Area Co-ordinators, and other teachers in the preparation and development of course teaching materials, teaching programmes, methods of teaching and assessments;
•	To ensure high standards of professional practice; quality of teaching and ongoing training; 
•	Through effective dialogue, participating in reciprocal peer review and observation.
•	To contribute to the professional development of new teachers according to arrangements agreed with the Head of Centre;
•	To nurture a culture where teachers view themselves essentially as facilitators of learning and reflective practitioners.

